org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.amp.diff

Class CategAmountCellProto

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.Cell
      • org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.amp.diff.CategAmountCellProto
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable, CategCell

    public class CategAmountCellProto
extends Cell
    a "proto cell": a class which contains all the data necessary to translate a transaction to CategAmountCell once one has been given a Calendar, Locale and a Currency. The process which transforms a CategAmountCellProto into a CategAmountCell is called materialization and is implemented in #materialize(AmpCurrency, CachingCalendarConverter, CurrencyConvertor, NiPrecisionSetting)

    • Method Detail

      • materialize

        public CategAmountCell materialize(AmpCurrency usedCurrency,
                                   CachingCalendarConverter calendarConverter,
                                   CurrencyConvertor currencyConvertor,
                                   NiPrecisionSetting precisionSetting,
                                   boolean isInformativeAmount)
        Materializes this instance into a full transaction. The operation is O(1) cheap because the heavyweight components of a cell are deeply immutable structures which are shared between with the prototype (namely, metaInfo and Cell.getCoordinates()) If the informativeAmount parameter is set to true, the amount will have the same value as the origAmount
        Parameters:
        usedCurrency - the AmpCurrency to use for converting the natural transaction to
        calendarConverter - the O(1) CalendarConverter to use for translating the natural transaction's date
        currencyConvertor - the O(1) CurrencyConvertor to use for for converting amounts between currencies
        precisionSetting - the precision settings to use while doing the amount conversions and to store in the generated MonetaryAmount
        isInformativeAmount - if the amount is informative (amount not converted) or not
        Returns:
